<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>TF Sycamore</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>Stock/Alliance</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=red&gt;HARD&lt;/color&gt;

The purpose of TF Sycamore is to gain and maintain sensor dominance. The Rod of Iron is a cruise missile silo armed with Shipwreck Is and IIs, which should be fired together against high-value targets with one II per salvo for maximum effect. The Eye of Providence is equipped with a long-range radar for maintaining track on the enemy and with its Vortex and Thundercloud missiles for striking light targets. Moving in advance of the frigates are two stealthy corvettes. Using their Bullseye FCRs on ELINT tracks enables precision strikes with their complement of deadly Whirlpool and Maelstrom missiles. The forward ships are covered by anti-craft missiles, Supercells for anti-spotter work and Eyewalls for use against fighters and bombers. TF Sycamore is best used to support teammates by destroying enemy spotters and damaging enemy combat ships as they engage friendly forces.
  </Description>
  <SortOverrideOrder>6</SortOverrideOrder>
